    "Additionally, under this classdependent assumption, we can distinguish two specific types of label noise: symmetric and asymmetric.For symmetric label noise [41], the corruption rate is uniform, meaningη ij = ηi K-1, ∀j ̸ = y and η i = η, ∀i ∈ [k],where the whole modeling is decided by a constant η.",
    "In this case, each label has an equal chance of being corrupted into any other label.For asymmetric label noise [14], [42], the noise rate η ij depends on both the true label i and the corrupted label j."
